ypes.TypedC.typ</a></span></code><div class=\"def-doc\"><span class=\"comment-delim\">(*</span><p>Used during interprocedural analysis to enter the entry function, but should be replaced the first time it is encountered</p><span class=\"comment-delim\">*)</span></div></li></ol></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-find_hook\"><a href=\"#val-find_hook\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> find_hook : <span><span class=\"xref-unresolved\">Binsec</span>.Virtual_address.t <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <a href=\"#type-hook\">hook</a> * string</span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Finds a hook, or raise Not_found.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-exploration_only\"><a href=\"#val-exploration_only\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> exploration_only : <span>bool <span class=\"xref-unresolved\">Stdlib</span>.ref</span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Says whether the analysis should be &quot;merge over all paths&quot; only. Initially false.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-kernel_exit_point\"><a href=\"#val-kernel_exit_point\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> kernel_exit_point : <span class=\"xref-unresolved\">Binsec</span>.Virtual_address.t</span></code></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-add_stop\"><a href=\"#val-add_stop\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> add_stop : <span><span class=\"xref-unresolved\">Binsec</span>.Virtual_address.t <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> unit</span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Add a hook to say that we should stop at this address.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-add_return_unknown\"><a href=\"#val-add_return_u